---
import BaseLayout from "@layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Methodology"
  description="Research, sourcing, completeness, and validation methodology."
>
  <section class="directory-hero py-14">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow">Methodology</p>
      <h1 class="section-title mt-3">How the archive earns trust</h1>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-archive card max-w-3xl p-6">
      <p>
        Records are built from official award pages first, then institutional
        pages, scholarly references, and carefully labelled secondary sources.
        Wikipedia may aid discovery but is not treated as the final authority
        for important claims.
      </p>
      <p>
        Completeness labels are part of the data model. A record marked in
        progress or requires verification should be read as useful but not
        finished. This is deliberate: transparent incompleteness is better than
        false certainty.
      </p>
      <p>
        Mathematical explanations are separated into plain-language, student,
        and advanced layers. The advanced layer points back to sources instead
        of pretending that a short archive summary replaces the technical
        literature.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
